2011-05-02T22:29:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/singapore-daybook-singapore-post-smrt-noble-group-longcheer.html
Singapore Post reported a near-10
percent decline in fourth-quarter net income and said it was
looking for acquisitions in Singapore and  Asia .  WHAT TO WATCH:  *Baker Technology Ltd. (BTL SP) said 1Q revenue rose 71% to
S$10.6m.
*Eratat Lifestyle (ERAT SP) said it won approval to list 15m new
shares at S$0.202 each.
*Longcheer Holdings Ltd. (LHL SP) said its 3Q net loss was 66.7m
yuan compared with a profit of 54.6m yuan a year earlier.
*Noble Group Ltd. (NOBL SP) said it agreed to invest in
infrastructure assets with Korea Investment Corp.
*Raffles Education Corp. (RLS SP) said it plans to get S$78m in
10-year financing from the IFC.
*Singapore Post Ltd. (SPOST SP) said 4Q net dropped 9.6% to
S$37m. The company said it is cautiously optimistic on its
outlook and is looking for acquisitions in Singapore and Asia.
*SMRT Corp. (MRT SP) reported a 50% rise in 4Q net to S$34m. The
company said it expects 1Q sales to increase while costs will
remain a challenge due to losses related to the launch of a new
train line as well as volatile fuel and power costs.  MARKETS:  S&P 500  down 0.2% to 1,361.22
Stoxx Europe 600 up 0.05% to 283.93
MSCI Asia Pacific up 1% to 140.82
Straits Times Index down 0.2% to 3,179.86  ELECTIONS:  Singapore politicians are campaigning ahead of May 7 elections.
